    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The Prospect Might seem bizarre, but I saw something similar in action after a pre-release, and I was stunned.<br />
<br />
Eomer is there to play Riddermark Soldiers as Skirmish events...<br />
Eowyn then uses the boost to win a skirmish...<br />
She also gets a boost from Theoden and Gandalf!<br />
So, everything ends up being quite strong.  Merry is there to add some muscle, since you&#39;re running a fair amount of companions.<br />
<br />
However, be sure to get Riddermark soldiers killed.  Yes, I said, KILLED.  Try to use them, then dispose of them before they can be used as an extra companion to the &quot;Spot 6 or more companions&quot; effects.  <br />
<br />
Two of your companions are Musterable so, 35 cards is no biggie.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
The Shadow is quite good:<br />
The Mouth of Sauron gets out your amazingly great Countless Companies, and you start to power up and power up more and more minions.  It&#39;s simple and effective.  The Strange Looking Men are there to make sure the skirmishes go more in your favor.  Grima makes an excellant addition, and allows you to really even the odds through exhaustion. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
